CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 10, 1961, page 19 reads: "Jackie Wilson Tours--Jackie Wilson, left, who's leaving them limp as he skyrockets to fame on a smooth lyrical kick, was in Pittsburgh this week on a promotional tour, meeting and greeting news reporters, disc jockeys and others along theatrical row. Above he is telling Porky Chedwick, wax waffle spinner of radio station WAMO, center, and old friend, the ever popular Roy Hamilton, right, who is appearing at a local nightclub about his latest hit album, "You Aint Heard Nothing Yet", during a luncheon at the Carleton House." -- Harris Photo.
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of four men standing, from left to right, manager Nat Tarnapol, Jackie Wilson, Porky Chedwick holding Jackie Wilson's "You Ain't Heard Nothin Yet" album, and Roy Hamilton at the Carleton House, another version
